Shape - Class in main.se450.model
Shape is the abstract base class for all shape contexts which allow the application to create and instantiate a shape, set its coordinates, direction of it's move function, and its individual strategy to implement when the shape contacts the extreme limits of the window on which the application is run.
Shape(float, float, float, float, float, float, float, int, IStrategy) - Constructor for class main.se450.model.Shape
The Shape(...) method instantiates the shape and sets its attributes.
ShapeFactory - Class in main.se450.factories
The ShapeFactory is a factory design class that allows the application to produce different shapes.
ShapeParser - Class in main.se450.parser
The parser for the shapes file
ShapeParser() - Constructor for class main.se450.parser.ShapeParser
 
strategicmove() - Method in interface main.se450.interfaces.IShape
Each shape will hold either a pass-through function or a rebound function.
strategicmove() - Method in class main.se450.model.Shape
